+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lg3nQ7uGSK27V4aJaRuRUt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully read all the TypeScript source files and test files. Here's a comprehensive summary of the codebase:\n\n## Full Codebase Overview\n\n### Source Files\n\n#### /workspace/src/index.ts\nMain export file that re-exports all public modules and types from the event-driven order processing system.\n\n#### /workspace/src/events/types.ts\nDefines event interfaces for the order processing pipeline:\n- `OrderEvent` (base interface)\n- `OrderCreatedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent`, `OrderRefundedEvent`\n- `PaymentChargedEvent`, `StockReservedEvent`\n- `ORDER_EVENTS` constant object with event type names\n\n#### /workspace/src/events/bus.ts\n**EventBus class** - implements event emitter pattern with:\n- Module-level `globalHandlers` Map shared across instances\n- `on(event, handler)` - registers handler\n- `off(event, handler)` - removes handler\n- `emit(event, data)` - fires all handlers for an event (async)\n- `clear()` - clears all handlers\n\n#### /workspace/src/orders/repository.ts\n**OrderRepository** - in-memory storage for orders:\n- `Order` interface with fields: id, customerId, items, status, total, discount, taxRate, createdAt, updatedAt, notes\n- `OrderStatus` type: 'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded'\n- Methods: `create()`, `findById()`, `update()`, `findByCustomer()`, `findByStatus()`, `clear()`\n\n#### /workspace/src/orders/service.ts\n**OrderService** - orchestrates order lifecycle:\n- Constructor takes: OrderRepository, EventBus, BillingService\n- `createOrder()` - creates order, emits CREATED event, charges payment, confirms order, emits CONFIRMED\n- `cancelOrder()` - emits CANCELLED event, updates status (only if 'confirmed')\n- `refundOrder()` - enforces 30-day refund window, calls billingService.issueRefund(), updates to 'refunded'\n- `getOrder()`, `getOrdersByCustome